{"word":"ἀκόρητος","slug":"ἀκόρητος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀκόρητος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κορέννυμι'><el>κορέννυμι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>insatiate, unsated in</i> or <i>with</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(<el>κορέω</el>) <i>unswept, ungrimmed, ungarnished</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}